All is well at Merica hotel in Nakuru as the minor fire that had broken out at the hotel this evening, was contained minutes after it started. Nakuru county fire brigade in conjunction with hotel staff and the police quickly put out the fire that started at around 6.15pm. Nakuru east deputy sub-county commander Fanton Analo says that every client and staff has been accounted for. On his part, the hotel manager john Lelaono insists that the hotel is ready to readmit its client.